cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing tasks and proposes a new neural method for handling Named Entities (NEs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper relies on learned word embeddings, which suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also evaluates its proposed method on a structured Question-Answering task, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper specifically addresses the difficulty of dealing with out of vocabulary (OOV) NEs, which could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
